d price will be refunded. If we change the price after you have paid for it, your subscription will not be affected until the expiration date.</p><p>Subscriptions do automatically renew. VREF makes no guarantee that you will be notified prior to or after your subscription expiration date. Upon subscription expiration, you may renew for another subscription period by visiting <a href=\u0022//www.VREF.com\u0022>www.VREF.com</a> or by calling our office at 844-303-VREF.</p><p>Should the <a href=\u0022//www.VREF.com\u0022>www.VREF.com</a> website go offline for more than 24 hours, your subscription will be extended by the duration of the downtime upon your request.</p><h2>USER / PATRON POLICY</h2><p>When communicating with any VREF representative and/or using the services and/or products on our Site, please conduct yourself in a manner that fosters goodwill and respectful consideration for yourself, others, the Content, and all VREF representatives.</p><p>We reserve the right to exercise, without limitation, the ability to monitor, block, intercede, edit, and/or ignore communication or commentary that is inconsistent with the sensibilities and standards of mutual respect and consideration and/or to protect proprietary information. Any action taken will only be done where necessary and appropriate to maintain site security, and atmosphere of interactive decorum that VREF, and its Website, <a href=\u0022//www.VREF.com\u0022>www.VREF.com</a>, requires providing outstanding service, goods, and satisfaction.</p><p>We try and ensure our websites are available for use 24 hours per day, seven days per week other than for a small period of scheduled downtime; however, we do not warrant that at different times our websites will be available. To the fullest extent permitted by law, we will not be liable to you for damages or refunds should our sites become unavailable or access to the Site becomes slow or incomplete due to system backup procedures, internet traffic volume, upgrades, an overload of requests to the servers, general network failures or delays, or any other cause which may from time to time make the any of our websites inaccessible to you.</p><h2>CHANGES, ADDITIONS, AND DELETIONS POLICY</h2><p>VREF, may change the Content on the Website, <a href=\u0022//www.VREF.com\u0022>www.VREF.com</a>, add, remove, and/or modify any terms or conditions of use of such Content, or remove or discontinue such Content altogether, at any time, and without prior notice.</p><p>If VREF makes any such changes, the revised Content will be placed on the Website with a revised publication date. Still, no other notice implied, statutory, and or assumed will be provided. VREF recommends the periodic review of all Content, Services, and Products, online policies, and similar documents to remain informed and up to date on areas relevant to your situation.</p><p>ALL Content, Services, and Products; ONLINE DOCUMENTATION, POLICIES, SOFTWARE, AND PROPRIETARY DOCUMENTS ARE FOR INFORMATIONAL PURPOSES ONLY. VREF MAKES NO WARRANTIES, EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY, BY POSTING SUCH DOCUMENTS OR ABOUT THE INFORMATION IN SUCH DOCUMENTS.</p><p>The information contained in <a href=\u0022//www.VREF.com\u0022>www.VREF.com</a> represents the current information available as of the date they are posted. Because VREF must respond to changing market conditions, legal statutes, accounting principles and practices, and other market forces, all information provided should not be interpreted as legally binding but rather as flexible documents subject to change. Due to these conditions and aforementioned market forces, VREF cannot guarantee or warrant that any information provided will be error-free or kept entirely up to date after they are posted.</p><p>ALL CONTENT, SERVICES, PRODUCTS, AND DOWNLOADS, POLICIES, SOFTWARE, AND PROPRIETARY DOCUMENTS ARE FOR INFORMATIONAL, PERSONAL, AND/OR NON-COMMERCIAL PURPOSES ONLY. VREF MAKES NO WARRANTIES, EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY, BY POSTI